{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"da939ff5-0760-4234-b26b-46cc270bba4b","content":"Here are the changes you need:\n\n**Dockerfile additions** (add before your `USER` switch):\n\n```dockerfile\n# Create dump directory writable by your app user\nRUN mkdir -p /tmp/dumps && chown app:app /tmp/dumps\n\n# Tell CoreCLR to write dumps on crash\nENV DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nENV DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4\nENV DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\n\nUSER app\n```\n\n`MiniDumpType` values: `1` = Mini, `2` = Heap, `3` = Triage, `4` = Full.\n\n**docker run command:**\n\n```bash\ndocker run --cap-add=SYS_PTRACE \\\n  -v /host/path/dumps:/tmp/dumps \\\n  your-image\n```\n\n`--cap-add=SYS_PTRACE` is required because `createdump` (the CoreCLR dump generator) uses `ptrace` to snapshot the process. Without it, dump collection silently fails. The volume mount lets you retrieve dumps from the host.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7b5f7e65-b30f-4206-b648-0a19164a6527","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up crash dump collection for a CoreCLR/.NET app in an Alpine-based Docker container running as a non-root user. I'll provide the Dockerfile changes and docker run command needed.\n\nKey considerations for Alpine + CoreCLR crash dumps:\n- Alpine uses musl libc, not glibc — createdump is the .NET tool for generating dumps\n- Need to set environment variables for crash dump collection\n- Non-root user needs write permissions to the dump directory\n- Need `ptrace` capability for createdump to work\n- SYS_PTRACE capability must be granted at `docker run` time\n\n\n- I'll use a dedicated directory for dumps rather than /tmp for better organization.","outputTokens":462,"requestId":"7851:2ED298:47B599:534C94:69FA9DF5"},"id":"43832fab-8058-423d-8a96-a74f9f7f82bd","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:48:48.077Z","parentId":"85dc47eb-1dad-4c4c-b981-857802ca35a3"}
